main event: A meteor-like rock was discovered in Englewood, Ohio, on May 30, 1955.
interesting points: The rock was extremely light-weight with a glassy formation and many small holes,The rock was black with white spots and had a portion of greenish color,Mr. [redacted] expressed a desire to analyze the rock further,The specimen was reportedly heated to extremely high temperatures,The rock was found in Mr. [redacted]'s garden early in the morning.
